### Control Flow

All control flow is **expression-based** (returns a value):

```hica
// if / else-if / else
let label = if n < 0 { "neg" } else if n == 0 { "zero" } else { "pos" }

// match â€” arms separated by commas, wildcard is `_`
fun classify(n: int) : string => match n {
  0             => "zero",
  x if x < 0   => "negative",
  1 | 2 | 3    => "small",
  _             => "other"
}

// Loops (statements, not expressions)
for i in 0..10 { println(i) }          // exclusive upper bound
for item in my_list { println(item) }  // iterate collection
while cond { ... }
repeat(3) { println("hi") }
```

Empty `else` branch: use `else { }` (empty block) â€” never write `else { () }`

